[http://travis-ci.org Travis CI] is a continuous integration service which can be used for automated testing of an Emacs Lisp library hosted on [[GitHub]].

[http://github.com/rolandwalker/emacs-travis emacs-travis] is a recipe for testing your library under multiple versions of Emacs.

[https://github.com/sshaw/build-status build-status] minor mode shows a buffer's build status in the mode line.


Also see [[CircleCI]] and [[Jenkins]].

